00:00:16.099 --> 00:00:18.101 position:50% align:center
[ICHIJOU] Since they're down a
runner, Summer's asked us

00:00:18.184 --> 00:00:19.436 position:50% align:center
to pick a sub.

00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:22.188 position:50% align:center
We gave it careful thought,
and ultimately decided

00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:23.857 position:50% align:center
on one of the first-years.

00:00:25.316 --> 00:00:26.776 position:50% align:center
But why one of them, ma'am?

00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:28.862 position:50% align:center
I'm sure it's disappointing
for you second-years,

00:00:28.945 --> 00:00:31.197 position:50% align:center
but this is our centennial,
so we went with someone

00:00:31.281 --> 00:00:32.741 position:50% align:center
from the 100th class.

00:00:32.824 --> 00:00:34.409 position:50% align:center
I hope you understand.

00:00:34.492 --> 00:00:37.662 position:50% align:center
We could have picked the
top student, but instead,

00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:40.540 position:50% align:center
we chose to go in
a different direction.

00:00:40.623 --> 00:00:45.712 position:50% align:center
And so Sarasa Watanabe,
we'll be counting on you!

00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:50.091 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:52.052 position:50% align:center
What?!

00:00:54.512 --> 00:00:57.515 position:50% align:center
[AI] Sarasa was chosen,
and the other girls

00:00:57.599 --> 00:00:58.892 position:50% align:center
weren't exactly thrilled.

00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:36.156 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
I mean, I'm cool with it, but...

00:02:36.239 --> 00:02:37.824 position:50% align:center
Why is Sarasa always
the one getting

00:02:37.907 --> 00:02:40.076 position:50% align:center
these awesome opportunities?

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:41.661 position:50% align:center
Normally they would've
gone by grades,

00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.705 position:50% align:center
which should've made
you their pick.

00:02:43.788 --> 00:02:45.957 position:50% align:center
The Superiors chose
who they chose.

00:02:46.041 --> 00:02:48.793 position:50% align:center
And remember, there's no such
thing as normal in our world.

00:02:48.877 --> 00:02:51.212 position:50% align:center
The second-years have already
been going hard on us.

00:02:51.296 --> 00:02:53.131 position:50% align:center
I hope this doesn't
make it worse.

00:02:58.303 --> 00:03:00.221 position:50% align:center
If it isn't the chosen one.

00:03:00.305 --> 00:03:01.723 position:50% align:center
Good morning!

00:03:01.806 --> 00:03:04.351 position:50% align:center
I thought you'd be too busy
with the festival to clean.

00:03:04.434 --> 00:03:05.643 position:50% align:center
Glad I was wrong.

00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:08.021 position:50% align:center
Good morning!
Of course, I'm happy to help!

00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:10.565 position:50% align:center
And I guess you're
on cleaning duty, too?

00:03:10.648 --> 00:03:11.941 position:50% align:center
Yeah, sure am.

00:03:12.025 --> 00:03:13.985 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI] Boy, the hundredth
class is just so lucky,

00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.153 position:50% align:center
don't you think?

00:03:15.236 --> 00:03:16.780 position:50% align:center
Have you met up with
the representatives

00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:18.448 position:50% align:center
from the Summer Troupe yet?

00:03:18.531 --> 00:03:19.991 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:22.577 position:50% align:center
Everyone who's participating in
the relay race got together.

00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:24.621 position:50% align:center
Their top star, Reo Shiina,
was there,

00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:26.247 position:50% align:center
and so was Aika Shion.

00:03:26.331 --> 00:03:28.333 position:50% align:center
Oh, and Jou Kisaragi, too.

00:03:28.416 --> 00:03:29.918 position:50% align:center
They say anything to you?

00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:32.212 position:50% align:center
Well, uh... "You're tall!"

00:03:32.295 --> 00:03:34.005 position:50% align:center
That was about
everything, though.

00:03:34.089 --> 00:03:36.216 position:50% align:center
Always getting noticed for
your above-average height,

00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:37.842 position:50% align:center
aren't you, Miss Watanabe?

00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:40.178 position:50% align:center
Kind of like a tree that
people only think is special

00:03:40.261 --> 00:03:41.846 position:50% align:center
because it's so tall.

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.932 position:50% align:center
Now, personally, I would
have picked Miss Narata,

00:03:44.015 --> 00:03:46.559 position:50% align:center
since people would love
seeing her out on stage.

00:03:46.643 --> 00:03:49.521 position:50% align:center
Although maybe that's why
they decided on you, instead.

00:03:49.604 --> 00:03:51.398 position:50% align:center
After all, we students can't
go around outshining

00:03:51.481 --> 00:03:53.692 position:50% align:center
the stars at such
a special event.

00:03:53.775 --> 00:03:55.902 position:50% align:center
So do your best not
to stand out, 'kay?

00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:58.321 position:50% align:center
Right! I'll try
super-duper hard!

00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:02.158 position:50% align:center
Oh, boy.
You totally missed the point.

00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:03.660 position:50% align:center
[SARASA yelps]

00:04:03.743 --> 00:04:06.788 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI] The idea is not to try
hard. Or even try at all.

00:04:06.871 --> 00:04:07.872 position:50% align:center
Get it?

00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:08.915 position:50% align:center
The only people who
should stand out

00:04:08.998 --> 00:04:10.792 position:50% align:center
are the actual troupe members.

00:04:10.875 --> 00:04:12.043 position:50% align:center
You can't help your height,

00:04:12.127 --> 00:04:14.462 position:50% align:center
but turn that big
personality down to zero.

00:04:14.546 --> 00:04:16.256 position:50% align:center
Nobody is there to see you!

00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:17.841 position:50% align:center
Become nothingness!

00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:22.429 position:50% align:center
[AI] I'm not sure if
anyone else noticed,

00:04:22.512 --> 00:04:25.515 position:50% align:center
but I could tell Sarasa
had taken those words

00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:27.392 position:50% align:center
far too literally.

00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:30.812 position:50% align:center
Become nothingness.

00:04:30.895 --> 00:04:33.857 position:50% align:center
A very wise person once said,

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:36.985 position:50% align:center
"Don't think, feel."
I can do that, right?

00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:39.112 position:50% align:center
Hey, back during your JPX days,

00:04:39.195 --> 00:04:42.198 position:50% align:center
did you ever get nervous
when you were out on stage?

00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.616 position:50% align:center
Are you nervous?

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:44.993 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:46.077 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Whoa.

00:04:47.328 --> 00:04:49.873 position:50% align:center
The thing is, I got used
to people staring at me

00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:52.125 position:50% align:center
from an early age.

00:04:52.208 --> 00:04:54.586 position:50% align:center
When I started
disliking the attention,

00:04:54.669 --> 00:04:56.671 position:50% align:center
I just sorta learned
how to filter it out.

00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:00.550 position:50% align:center
If I work at it, maybe
I can develop a filter

00:05:00.633 --> 00:05:03.928 position:50% align:center
of my own before
the Sports Festival.

00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:07.724 position:50% align:center
Honestly, Sarasa, I don't think
that's the best approach.

00:05:07.807 --> 00:05:10.560 position:50% align:center
I realized something,
back when we were doing

00:05:10.643 --> 00:05:12.312 position:50% align:center
Romeo and Juliet.

00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:14.856 position:50% align:center
Mr. Andou's reaction
gave it away.

00:05:14.939 --> 00:05:17.567 position:50% align:center
Pretend that you're paying
attention to the audience,

00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:20.236 position:50% align:center
and they'll see
right through it.

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:22.489 position:50% align:center
Ignoring them won't
really work, either.

00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:25.909 position:50% align:center
You're up there to create a
connection, not distance.

00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:28.244 position:50% align:center
You have to consider
what they're looking for,

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:31.414 position:50% align:center
what it is they want to see
and remain conscious of that

00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.041 position:50% align:center
while you're up on stage.

00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:37.837 position:50% align:center
Consider what the
audience wants to see?

00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.757 position:50% align:center
I don't think anyone wants
to see me out there!

00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:42.217 position:50% align:center
What am I gonna do?

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:44.386 position:50% align:center
[whines]

00:05:44.469 --> 00:05:47.847 position:50% align:center
[AI] Why am I so bad at
this "cheering up" stuff?

00:05:47.931 --> 00:05:50.433 position:50% align:center
[AI] Soon, the day of
the Festival arrived.

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:54.604 position:50% align:center
The Spring Troupe is
raring and ready to go!

00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:56.398 position:50% align:center
Summer for win two!

00:05:56.481 --> 00:05:58.483 position:50% align:center
The Autumn Troupe
is going for the gold!

00:05:58.566 --> 00:06:00.235 position:50% align:center
Winter's gonna give it our all!

00:06:00.318 --> 00:06:03.863 position:50% align:center
Let's do this! The
Superior-Student team is here!

00:06:03.947 --> 00:06:07.450 position:50% align:center
[AI] Elegance and restraint,
Kouka fans demonstrate both,

00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:11.037 position:50% align:center
even at their most passionate,
but once every ten years,

00:06:11.121 --> 00:06:14.457 position:50% align:center
that changes here at the
Kouka Grand Sports Festival.

00:06:14.541 --> 00:06:15.834 position:50% align:center
Well, folks, it's here:

00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:18.086 position:50% align:center
the moment that we've
spent a decade waiting for.

00:06:18.169 --> 00:06:21.214 position:50% align:center
Introducing this
year's combatants!

00:06:21.297 --> 00:06:22.757 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE cheers]

00:06:22.841 --> 00:06:26.052 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] From the
Spring Troupe, Ryuu Asahina!

00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:29.097 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER] From the
Summer Troupe, Reo Shiina!

00:06:29.180 --> 00:06:32.100 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] From the Autumn
Troupe, Keito Mitsuki!

00:06:32.183 --> 00:06:35.895 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER] From the Winter
Troupe, Sei Satomi!

00:06:35.979 --> 00:06:37.105 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B]
Last but not least,

00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:39.149 position:50% align:center
the Superior-Student team!

00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:43.778 position:50% align:center
Now, our Troupe
representatives will lead

00:06:43.862 --> 00:06:46.406 position:50% align:center
the combatants in
the honor pledge!

00:06:46.489 --> 00:06:49.034 position:50% align:center
On this day, we give our pledge.

00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:51.494 position:50% align:center
To uphold the true Kouka spirit!

00:06:51.578 --> 00:06:54.205 position:50% align:center
To compete gallantly,
fairly, and beautifully!

00:06:54.289 --> 00:06:56.916 position:50% align:center
To represent our troupes
with our whole hearts!

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.002 position:50% align:center
We offer you our solemn vow.

00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:00.754 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE cheers]

00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:04.674 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA] Our first festival
entrance ceremony.

00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:05.675 position:50% align:center
Wasn't it awesome?

00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:07.218 position:50% align:center
[CHIAKI]
Mm-hmm.

00:07:07.302 --> 00:07:09.637 position:50% align:center
And it sounded like everybody
really liked our dance, too!

00:07:09.721 --> 00:07:12.474 position:50% align:center
That was better than all our
rehearsals, don't you think?

00:07:12.557 --> 00:07:14.017 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:16.019 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI] Miss Watanabe, you were
looking a little bit sloppy

00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.771 position:50% align:center
during the second
verse's choreo.

00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:19.189 position:50% align:center
Whoops, sorry!

00:07:19.272 --> 00:07:21.066 position:50% align:center
We need someone
to prep the flags.

00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.317 position:50% align:center
Think you can help me?

00:07:22.400 --> 00:07:23.902 position:50% align:center
Sure!

00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:25.320 position:50% align:center
Hey, it'll go faster with two--

00:07:25.403 --> 00:07:26.738 position:50% align:center
No thank you!

00:07:26.821 --> 00:07:28.281 position:50% align:center
She asked me specifically
because only second-years

00:07:28.365 --> 00:07:30.283 position:50% align:center
are supposed to
help with events.

00:07:30.367 --> 00:07:31.451 position:50% align:center
And of those second-years,

00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:33.078 position:50% align:center
only those who are
considered most capable

00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:34.120 position:50% align:center
get the honor.

00:07:34.204 --> 00:07:36.956 position:50% align:center
As determined by their grades.

00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:39.501 position:50% align:center
And as I recall,
yours aren't the best.

00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:40.377 position:50% align:center
[SUPERIOR A]
Hijiri!

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:41.920 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI]
Well, I'd better go!

00:07:44.506 --> 00:07:46.216 position:50% align:center
This has gone far enough.

00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:48.927 position:50% align:center
You seriously need to stop
messing with that girl.

00:07:49.010 --> 00:07:51.471 position:50% align:center
You're going to stunt
her growth as a student.

00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:53.264 position:50% align:center
I'm not messing with her.

00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.684 position:50% align:center
Just working out a little
jealousy, that's all.

00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:56.935 position:50% align:center
You're jealous of her?

00:07:57.852 --> 00:08:00.188 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI] She always stands out,
and everyone expects

00:08:00.271 --> 00:08:02.440 position:50% align:center
great things from her.

00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.192 position:50% align:center
And then there's the fact
that she's best friends

00:08:04.275 --> 00:08:06.986 position:50% align:center
with my darling Naracchi,
which is so unfair.

00:08:07.070 --> 00:08:07.987 position:50% align:center
What?

00:08:08.071 --> 00:08:10.031 position:50% align:center
My God, Hijiri, you are such a--

00:08:10.115 --> 00:08:11.866 position:50% align:center
A bitch, Risa?

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:13.410 position:50% align:center
Well, sure.

00:08:13.493 --> 00:08:16.454 position:50% align:center
But only by accident, so it
doesn't really count, does it?

00:08:16.538 --> 00:08:17.706 position:50% align:center
You should go.

00:08:17.789 --> 00:08:19.958 position:50% align:center
Why waste time here when
Miss Watanabe needs you?

00:08:20.041 --> 00:08:21.668 position:50% align:center
She seemed so upset.

00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:25.338 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] No matter
who you're rooting for,

00:08:25.422 --> 00:08:27.632 position:50% align:center
I think we all agree that
our troupes look lovely

00:08:27.716 --> 00:08:29.175 position:50% align:center
taking the field.

00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:31.553 position:50% align:center
Now, the Giant Ball Roll!

00:08:31.636 --> 00:08:33.763 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER] Their path will lead
them down the silver bridge

00:08:33.847 --> 00:08:36.266 position:50% align:center
to the finish line,
in the fast and furious

00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:38.727 position:50% align:center
75-meter race!

00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:40.603 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B]
Look at that kick line go.

00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.397 position:50% align:center
They've really caught
the spirit of the day.

00:08:42.480 --> 00:08:43.690 position:50% align:center
[whistle]

00:08:44.816 --> 00:08:47.068 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER]
Now: The Dancing Ball Toss!

00:08:47.152 --> 00:08:49.112 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] You won't find
events like these anywhere

00:08:49.195 --> 00:08:51.364 position:50% align:center
but with the Kouka troupe!

00:08:51.448 --> 00:08:52.907 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER] Let's see what
the scoreboard looks like

00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:54.242 position:50% align:center
at halftime:

00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:57.370 position:50% align:center
In first place, the Summer
Troupe, with 83 points!

00:08:57.454 --> 00:09:01.583 position:50% align:center
Behind them in second
is Spring with 67 points!

00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:03.418 position:50% align:center
And next we have the cheer-off!

00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:05.545 position:50% align:center
First up, let's see what the
Superior-Student team

00:09:05.628 --> 00:09:07.505 position:50% align:center
will be performing.

00:09:07.589 --> 00:09:10.383 position:50% align:center
We'll play "Amongst the
Cherry Blossoms in the Wind,"

00:09:10.467 --> 00:09:13.094 position:50% align:center
our beloved school song. Ready?

00:09:13.178 --> 00:09:15.430 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:17.349 position:50% align:center
[music continues]

00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:08.233 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE cheers]

00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:09.275 position:50% align:center
[KOUZABUROU]
Wonderful!

00:10:09.359 --> 00:10:11.152 position:50% align:center
What a charming performance.

00:10:11.236 --> 00:10:13.947 position:50% align:center
Though I wonder why she's
not her usual, energetic self.

00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:19.119 position:50% align:center
[HIJIRI]
Huh. I don't see Tomomi.

00:10:19.202 --> 00:10:20.912 position:50% align:center
Well, I guess I have no choice.

00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:23.957 position:50% align:center
Miss Narata, will you
come help me, please?

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:25.667 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.293 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE E]
Look, it's Naracchi!

00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:29.462 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE F]
She's so cute!

00:10:29.546 --> 00:10:32.382 position:50% align:center
[AUDIENCE G] The second-year
with her is pretty adorable too!

00:10:32.465 --> 00:10:35.260 position:50% align:center
Not just a bitch, but a
conniving little rat, too.

00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:37.887 position:50% align:center
Naracchi doesn't seem
nervous out there at all.

00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:39.472 position:50% align:center
Are you okay, Sarasa?

00:10:39.556 --> 00:10:40.932 position:50% align:center
Don't worry, you didn't mess up!

00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:42.392 position:50% align:center
You're good!

00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:43.852 position:50% align:center
No, I'm not.

00:10:43.935 --> 00:10:47.480 position:50% align:center
I think I actually did something
worse than messing up.

00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:52.318 position:50% align:center
It's embarrassing, but I was so
scared of messing up that I--

00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:54.946 position:50% align:center
I didn't even play my recorder!

00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.449 position:50% align:center
Superior Ichijou,
we've got a problem!

00:10:57.532 --> 00:10:59.200 position:50% align:center
Miss Watanabe just admitted
she's been feeling

00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:00.410 position:50% align:center
a little bit off.

00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:03.079 position:50% align:center
Oh! Do you think a break
would help her out?

00:11:03.163 --> 00:11:04.539 position:50% align:center
Yes, I think that it would.

00:11:04.622 --> 00:11:05.623 position:50% align:center
Thank you very much, ma'am.

00:11:05.707 --> 00:11:07.000 position:50% align:center
We'll be back in ten, then.

00:11:08.793 --> 00:11:09.878 position:50% align:center
[RISA]
Okay, what's up?

00:11:09.961 --> 00:11:11.546 position:50% align:center
You've been acting
weird this whole time!

00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:13.214 position:50% align:center
I don't know, it's like...

00:11:13.298 --> 00:11:15.884 position:50% align:center
